<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--ChineseStudent     08-18 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Chinese Student,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chinese Student Leader to be Visiting Student at Harvard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of the leaders of the student
pro-democracy movement in China will be a visiting undergraduate
student at Harvard College during the 1989-90 school year, Harvard
officials said.
   Wu'er Kaixi was chairman of the Beijing Universities Students
Autonomous United Association, the unofficial union that coordinated
the majority of student demonstrations in Tianenmen Square.
   The visiting undergraduate program is aimed at students who want
to spend one semester or one academic year studying at Harvard.
About 35 students are enrolled each term in the program.
   Wu'er is expected to take two classes in the first term and three
classes in the second term, including courses in English, math,
social science and Chinese, officials said Thursday.
</TEXT>
