<FIRST>u i PM-Poland-Powers     08-18 0339</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poland-Powers,0357</SECOND>
<HEAD>Powers of the Polish President and Prime Minister</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Poland, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are brief descriptions of the powers
and duties of the president and prime minister in Poland:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>PRESIDENT</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   The president is the head of state and commander-in-chief of the
armed forces.
   Chosen by a joint vote of the Sejm and Senate, a president may
declare a state of war or a state of emergency when he judges that a
security threat exists, and rule for up to three months without the
consent of the Sejm, the lower house of parliament.
   He must ratify or consent to abrogate international agreements.
He also appoints and recalls ambassadors. He may veto legislation
passed by the Sejm, subject to a two-thirds majority override.
   He may dissolve parliament and call new elections in strictly
limited circumstances, for instance if parliament fails to choose a
government or pass a budget within three months of being seated, or
if parliament passes laws curtailing the president's powers.
   The presidency was restored this year after a 37-year absence.
Former Communist Party leader Wojciech Jaruzelski now holds the
office. The president serves a six-year term and may run once for
re-election.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>PRIME MINISTER</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   The prime minister is the head of government.
   Nominated by the president and elected by a simple majority of
the Sejm, the prime minister assembles a Cabinet to direct the
activities of the government and runs the ministries that control
Poland's state-sector-dominated economy. The Cabinet must also be
approved by the Sejm.
   The prime minister is responsible for the day-to-day actions of
government and also drafts and proposes laws to the parliament.
Other duties include drafting annual budgets and national plans for
the economy.
   The prime minister leads the weekly meetings of the Cabinet,
known as the Council of Ministers, and controls all important
government personnel decisions.
   The prime minister serves for the four-year term of the Sejm,
unless he is recalled by the president and voted out of office by a
majority of the Sejm.
</TEXT>
