<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--CouponBonanza     08-18 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Coupon Bonanza,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Couple Finds 254 Coupons in One Can of Coffee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SULPHUR, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple is going to have to drink a lot of
java between now and 1991 to redeem all the coupons they found in a
single can of coffee.
   Joyce and Dwight Spates recently found 254 discount coupons
totalling $101.60 in a 1-pound can of Sanka brand coffee.
   ``Joyce was making coffee for friends, and there was a coupon in
the first scoop out of a newly opened can, then another in the next
scoop until she had pulled out three or four coupons,'' Spates said
Thursday.
   They emptied the coffee into a bowl and ended up with half a can
of coffee and half a can of 40-cent coupons.
   Spates said he called the maker of Sanka to report the coupon
bonanza.
   ``I told the man who answered the phone at General Foods that we
don't usually drink Sanka coffee and asked him if all the cans have
this many coupons in them,'' Spates said.
</TEXT>
