<FIRST>r a PM-LightningDeaths     08-18 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lightning Deaths,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Men Sitting in Metal Chairs Killed by Lightning</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATESVILLE, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men sitting in metal lounge chairs
were struck and killed by lightning at the Sardis Lake dam,
officials said.
   Panola County Medical Examiner Clyde Cobb said efforts to revive
the men Thursday afternoon failed. Killed were Jeffrey L. Russell,
25, and James N. Mauney Jr., 29, both of Batesville.
   ``From the investigation that I've been able to do so far, they
were apparently laying out on metal lounge chairs and so they were
grounded with the metal,'' said Ms. Cobb. ``I don't know why they
stayed out there because there was a pretty bad cloud coming up.''
   Delbert Hearn, owner of Hearn's Trading Post, across the lake's
spillway from where the two were killed, said the storm that
produced the lightning was severe. He said the lightning struck
before the storm.
   ``It wasn't even raining yet. We could hear the thunder in the
distance,'' he said.
</TEXT>
