<FIRST>r a PM-USAToday-Editor     08-18 0109</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-USA Today-Editor,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sports Editor Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARLINGTON, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gene Policinski has been named managing
editor for sports at Gannett Co.'s USA Today, the newspaper said
today.
   Policinski, who has been deputy managing editor in the paper's
sports section since 1985, replaces Henry Freeman, who earlier this
week was named editor of Gannett's Wilmington (Del.) News-Journal
newspapers.
   Policinski, 38, joined USA Today in 1982 during its planning
stages. He was Washington editor and page one editor before moving
to sports.
   He joined Gannett in 1972 as a reporter for the Marion (Ind.)
Chronicle Tribune. In 1980 he became a national reporter for Gannett
News Service in Washington.
</TEXT>
