<SECOND>AM-People-Cher, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0595,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cher After Dark on MTV</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 2nd graf to delete extraneous words from quote.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MTV has decided to air Cher's video ``If I Could
Turn Back Time'' at night only, saying the Oscar-winning actress
shows ``a little too much tush'' in the clip.
   ``When we accepted it, we felt it was borderline,'' Abbey
Konowitch, MTV vice president for programming, said Friday. ``We
received a great deal of negative feedback from our audience. In
response, we've changed the way we're programming it.''
   The video, which premiered six weeks ago on MTV, will only be
aired from 9 p.m. to 6 a.m., said Konowitch. The clip features Cher
_ wearing a thin, carefully-placed V-shaped outfit and sheer
stockings _ performing on the deck of a troop ship.
   Her manager, Bill Sammeth, said MTV's decision was like closing
the barn door after the horse was gone: ``They think it shows too
much of her, but they allowed it for eight weeks.''
   Konowitch, however, had the final word: ``The video has a little
too much tush for a Saturday morning.''
</TEXT>
