<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Britain-Embassy     08-18 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Britain-Embassy,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Explode Package Found Near Indonesian Embassy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Friday blew up a suspicious package found
outside the Indonesian Embassy, which is several hundred yards away
from the U.S. Embassy.
   A spokeman for Scotland Yard said it was not known if the package
contained explosives but authorities evacuated the immediate area as
a precaution. Police blew up the parcel where it was found.
   The U.S. Embassy, on an adjoining side of Grosvenor Square, was
not evacuated, said an embassy spokesman.
   The Scotland Yard officer said the package was found at about 2
p.m. and it was blown up an hour later in a controlled explosion.
   ``It was blown up by our bomb squad but that doesn't mean it was
a bomb,'' he said. ``We're awaiting further details.''
</TEXT>
