<FIRST>r a AM-PlantExplosion     08-18 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Plant Explosion,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Killed, Five Injured in Explosives Plant Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOPLIN, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A blast at a commercial explosives plant
Friday killed two workers and injured five, officials said.
   The explosion occurred about 4:40 p.m. when the employees poured
molten primer into a 1-pound mold. The solidified primer is used to
ignite blasting agents, said Peter Astrauskas, technical director of
the Atlas Powder Co.
   The company did not identify the victims Friday night pending
notification of their relatives, Astrauskas said. The plant is five
miles east of Joplin.
   Astrauskas said the cause of the explosion would be investigated.
He said there was no fire and little damage to the plant.
   The injured were taken to St. John's Medical Center in Joplin,
where officials refused to disclose their conditions.
   Astrauskas said he knew of no fatal accidents at the plant since
just after World War II. The factory employs about 400 people and
makes explosives of various types, he said.
</TEXT>
