<FILEID>AP-NR-08-18-89 1233EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-PersonalComputers     08-18 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Personal Computers,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>GE Is Biggest Personal Computer User, Survey Finds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Electric Co. is the biggest corporate
user of personal computers, not counting the computer makers
themselves, according to a magazine survey.
   GE has 45,000 personal computers installed, with a ratio of 6.71
employees per PC, Personal Computing magazine says in its September
issue.
   International Business Machines Corp. and American Telephone &amp;
Telegraph Co. both had more PCs _ 200,000 and 129,000, respectively
_ but the survey excluded most companies that sell personal
computers as well as government bodies and schools.
   Here is the magazine's top 10:
   1. General Electric Co., 45,000 personal computers, 6.71
