<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Gateway     08-18 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Gateway,0185</SECOND>
<HEAD>Isosceles and Newgateway Reach Truce Over Gateway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Isosceles PLC, which last month beat rival bidder
Newgateway PLC for majority control of British supermarket operator
Gateway Corp. PLC, said Friday it has reached a truce with its
rival, which still has a 40-percent holding in Gateway.
   Under the truce, Newgateway, which comprises U.S. financiers
Wasserstein Perella and Co. and the Great Atlantic and Pacific Tea
Co., will exchange its holding for a proportionate stake in
Isoceles. It will have representation on Gateway's board of
directors, and will support Isosceles in implementing ``its
commercial strategy.''
   Newgateway is forbidden to increase its holding above 49.8
percent, unless Isosceles' board backs such a move.
   Newgateway lifted its stake in Gateway to the 40-percent level
after losing the takeover contest last month. This holding
represented a potential block to Isosceles' reorganization plans for
Gateway.
   Isosceles, made up of a group of disgruntled Gateway
shareholders, won the contest with a bid valuing Gateway at between
2.05 billion pounds, or $3.2 billion, and 2.23 billion pounds, or
$3.5 billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
