<FIRST>r f AM-AmocoGuarantee     08-18 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Amoco Guarantee,0214</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amoco Offering Guarantee with its Top Gasoline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amoco Oil Co. is preparing to offer a guarantee to
motorists, contending that its expensive Ultimate Premium gasoline
won't damage a car's fuel system.
   The oil company says this will be the only gasoline with its own
written guarantee, but critics say it's not much of a bargain.
   ``Gasolines typically don't cause problems unless, for instance,
water gets in the fuel tank,'' said Charles Sherwood, a Ford Motor
Co. product design engineer.
   Amoco said that beginning Monday it will reimburse car owners for
repairs of any fuel system damage caused by gasoline in which the
owner has used Ultimate Premium regularly in a new car. The
guarantee is good through the first 75,000 miles of operation or
until the car is sold or contract terminated for leased cars.
   The guarantee applies to cars, vans, light trucks or light-duty
four-wheel-drive vehicles, and covers repairs to such parts as fuel
injectors, carburetors, intake valves and ports, intake manifold,
fuel pump, fuel injection pump, fuel regulator, fuel rail, fuel
lines and fuel tank sending unit.
   Owners and lessees can register for the guarantee on forms
available in Amoco stations.
   Amoco Ultimate has a detergent additive.
</TEXT>
